# FAQ Backend System

This is a **backend API** for managing FAQs with multilingual support.  
It allows users to create, retrieve, update, and delete FAQs while providing translations in different languages.  
The system uses **Node.js, Express.js, MongoDB, Redis, and Google Translate API**.  

---

## 🚀 Features  

✅ Create, Read, Update, and Delete (CRUD) FAQs  
✅ Multilingual support (English, Hindi, Bengali)  
✅ Caching with Redis for better performance  
✅ WYSIWYG Editor support for rich-text answers  
✅ REST API with Express.js  

---

## 🛠️ Installation Steps  

### 🔹 **1. Clone the Repository**  
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/faq-backend.git
cd faq-backend

 🔹 2. Install Dependencies
npm install

  🔹 3. Set Up Environment Variables
PORT=3000
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://rohit1osc:0VuPaBi3Ti4MMChd@cluster0.fgmzs.mongodb.net/
REDIS_HOST=localhost
REDIS_PORT=6379
GOOGLE_TRANSLATE_API_KEY=your_google_translate_api_key

🔹 4. Start the Server
npm start



📌 API Usage Examples
🔹 1. Get All FAQs
GET http://localhost:3000/api/faqs
🔹 2. Add a New FAQ
POST http://localhost:3000/api/faqs
Request Body (JSON)
{
  "question": "What is Node.js?",
  "answer": "Node.js is a JavaScript runtime built on Chrome's V8 engine."
}
🔹 3. Update an FAQ
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/faqs/:id
Request Body (JSON)
{
  "question": "What is Express.js?",
  "answer": "Express.js is a web application framework for Node.js."
}
🔹 4. Delete an FAQ
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/faqs/:id



